    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_zs.00336.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>                 
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Medical Superintendent's</name>
                    <name type="place">Office.</name>
                    <name type="place">INSANE ASYLUM</name>
                    <name type="place">LONDON ONTARIO<ptr target="loc.08133_n4"/></name> 
                    <date when="1891-04-03"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>3 April <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>91</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your good long letter of March 30 and 31<ptr target="loc.08133_n1"/> came to hand last evening and would have been answered before now (7 p.m.) but work
                has been more than ordinarily pressing. I am greatly pleased to hear of even the most remote "indications of better" and trust
                they will increase. From all I can make out D<hi rend="underline">r</hi> Longaker<ptr target="loc.08039_n2"/> is a mighty level headed fellow and is likely to do well for you. 
                Your package containing "Munyon"<ptr target="loc.08133_n2"/> and "Youths Comp"<ptr target="loc.08133_n3"/> with the little poems 
                (one in facsimile) came today and was welcome. I have (of course) the Atlantic (take it) with O'C.'s<ptr target="n2002"/> 
                "Android"<ptr target="loc.02472_n9"/>&#8212;the more I see 
                &#38; know of O'C. the more I regret he did not fulfill his original intention of following literature as a profession&#8212;what 
                a proud row of books we might have had from him on our shelves today! 
                All goes quietly and well here including the meter<ptr target="loc.07230_n2"/>&#8212;</p>   
            <closer>
                <salute>So long!</salute>
                <salute>Best love</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer> 
        </body> 
    </text>
